{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSExpression","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSExpression","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" * ","kind":"text"},{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"text":". Set this property to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" to reset it to the default value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Constant ","type":"text"},{"code":"MLNHillshadeMethod","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Any of the following constant string values:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"standard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": The legacy hillshade method.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"basic"},{"text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"text":" default algorithm.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combined"},{"text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to GDAL’s "},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"code":"-combined","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"igor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"code":"-igor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"multidirectional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Hillshade with multiple illumination directions. Uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the basic hillshade model with multiple independent light sources.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Predefined functions, including mathematical and string operators","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Conditional expressions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Variable assignments and references to assigned variables","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Step functions applied to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"text":" variable","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property does not support applying interpolation functions to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"type":"text","text":" variable or applying interpolation or step functions to feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attributes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The hillshade algorithm to use, one of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodStandard"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodBasic"},{"text":", ",